               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gadla Takla Hāymānot “Vita of Takla Haymanot” (fols. 5ra-100vb)
                     II) Taʾammǝra Takla Hāymānot “Miracles of Takla Haymanot”: 20 miracles (fols.
                     101ra-117vb).</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The text of the Vita represents the first of the two sub-types of the
                        Dabra Libānos recension of the Gadla Takla Hāymānot (close, but not
                        identical to the published text of the Vita, s. <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/8SCM474J"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1906Taklahaymanot"/><title level="m">The Life of Takla Hâymânôt, in the version of Dabra Lîbanôs, and The Miracles of Takla Hâymânôt in the version of Dabra Lîbanôs, and The Book of the Riches of Kings</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">E. A. Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Privately printed for Lady Meux</publisher><date>1906</date><note type="url">https://archive.org/details/gri_33125012259343/page/n11/mode/2up</note></bibl>).</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
