                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre, but careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>
                        Scribe: Gabra Mikāʾel. The name of
                        the scribe, Gabra Mikāʾel, is mentioned in the supplication formulas on
                           <locus target="#82va">82va-</locus>vb, 111vb, 115arb, 100va,
                           117rb.<date>19th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the protagonist and other
                           saints; name of the scribe; incipits of Text I and its subsections (fols.
                           5r, 15va, 17ra, 21va, 26va, 36ra, 39ra, 42vb, 45vb, 45vb, 47ra, 65rb,
                           74ra, 82vb, 88va, 90vb, 91rb, 92vb, 93rb, 95ra, 97va); incipit of Text II
                           and its subsections (fols. 101r, 105ra, 106rb, 106vb, 107ra, 109va,
                           110ra, 110va, 111ra, 111vb, 112vb, 113va, 114ra, 114rb, 114vb, 115rb,
                           115vb, 115arb, 116ra, 116va); notes in the upper margin of some fols.;
                           elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals;
                           elements of the quire marks.
 On the incipit pages of Text I, some of
                           its subsections and of Text II (fols. 5r, 36r, 82vb, 101r), a few lines
                           are rubricated (alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
